<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Single_part_representation_arm  Rule: part_requires_version 
   <express_ref linkend="single_part_representation:arm:Single_part_representation_arm.part_requires_version"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Single_part_representation_arm.part_requires_version">
The <b>part_requires_version</b> rule ensures that each instance of
	<express_ref linkend="part_and_version_identification:arm:Part_and_version_identification_arm.Part">
		Part</express_ref> is referenced by at least one instance of 
	<express_ref linkend="part_and_version_identification:arm:Part_and_version_identification_arm.Part_version">
		Part_version</express_ref>. 
	<p>This rule enforces the requirement for every 
	<express_ref linkend="part_and_version_identification:arm:Part_and_version_identification_arm.Part">
		Part</express_ref> to have at least one 
	<express_ref linkend="part_and_version_identification:arm:Part_and_version_identification_arm.Part_version">
		Part_version</express_ref> associated to it.
</p>
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Single_part_representation_arm  Entity: part_requires_version  Where: WR1 
   <express_ref linkend="single_part_representation:arm:Single_part_representation_arm.part_requires_version.wr:WR1"/>

  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Single_part_representation_arm.part_requires_version.wr:WR1">
Each instance of <express_ref linkend="part_and_version_identification:arm:Part_and_version_identification_arm.Part">
		Part</express_ref> shall be referred to by one or more instances of 
	<express_ref linkend="part_and_version_identification:arm:Part_and_version_identification_arm.Part_version">
		Part_version</express_ref> through their of_product attribute.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Single_part_representation_arm  Rule: part_requires_id_owner 
   <express_ref linkend="single_part_representation:arm:Single_part_representation_arm.part_requires_id_owner"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Single_part_representation_arm.part_requires_id_owner">
The <b>part_requires_id_owner</b> rule constrains each <b>Part</b> to have an <b>Organization</b> or a 
<b>Person_in_organization</b> that owns its identifier.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Single_part_representation_arm  Entity: part_requires_id_owner  Where: WR1 
   <express_ref linkend="single_part_representation:arm:Single_part_representation_arm.part_requires_id_owner.wr:WR1"/>

  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Single_part_representation_arm.part_requires_id_owner.wr:WR1">
There shall not be any instance of <b>Part</b> that is not referred to by exactly one instance of 
<b>Organization_or_person_in_organization_assignment</b> with role 'id owner'.
</ext_description>
